The paper discusses the design of a multi-agent system (MAS) for controlling network packet routing, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The focus of the paper is on adaptivity in both the individual agents and the interaction structure among the agents, which is a key aspect of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, specifically reinforcement learning, in designing the agents' action spaces, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for the agents to learn their settings when the agent interaction structure is itself adaptive, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
